VA. RAMALINGA SASTRYA vocal recital by Mutnuri Jalajakshi, accompanied by her son and violinist Srinivasa Narasimha Murty and K. Gnananandam on mridangam, both AIR staffers, was organised by the management committee of Sri Sadgurubraha Sri Ramadoota Mandiram at its premises last week.Getting off to a scintillating start withHamsadvani varnam, Jalajakshi regaled all alike renderingGirija Ramana (Gambhira nata), Balakanakamaya (Athana) withswaram,Sri Naradanaadasaraseeruha (Kanada)prefixed with captivatingaalapana, Nenarinchinaanu (Maalavi),expansive expatiation ofNijadaasavarada (Kalyani)and an adroitly structuredragam, tanamandpallaviinSurati.Murty, in his turns and amiable following along with Gnananandam who executed an exquisiteThani, contributed grandeur.Earlier in the week, the premises witnessed a well structured vocal by the young artiste Kasturi Kamaladeepti. It was organised by noted veena artiste  Bhamidipati Kanakadurga Prasad in memory of his paternal grand mother Kameswari under the aegis of Sangeetha Kalaasamithi.Winner of many a laurel, both in playing the veena and rendering vocal from almost all prestigious sangeetha sabhas from all over the south from a young age, Deepti is now honing her skills under the tutelage of vocalist Pantula Rama. No wonder, she exhibited exquisite talent in the expression ofManodharmabesides rendering the compositions commensurably withbhava. The highlight of the evening wasragam, tanamandpallaviinSankarabharanamrendered with felicitous charm. She was ably accompanied on violin by G.V.S. Raghuram and G. Venkatesh on mridangam.Bottom Template Starts
